    scripture: "Therefore if any man be in Christ, he is a new creature: old things are passed away; behold, all things are become new.",
    walk: `Welcome, friend. Something has happened to you that the angels rejoice over — you have come to Jesus. And the very first thing God wants you to know is not a rule to keep or a task to do. It's who you now are. In Christ, you are a new creation. Not a patched-up version of the old you. Not the same person trying harder. New.

Read those words again slowly: old things are passed away. The guilt you carried, the labels other people gave you, the things you did in the dark and swore you'd never escape — God is not asking you to drag those into this new life. Jesus already carried them to the cross. They are passed. Behind you. The slate is not just wiped; you've been made brand new.

You may not feel new yet, and that's alright. Feelings catch up later. The truth came first, and the truth doesn't depend on your feelings — it depends on what Jesus did. You are in Christ now, and that changes everything about you at the root, even on the days your heart is slow to believe it.

So this walk you're beginning doesn't start with you climbing up to God. It starts with God reaching down and making you new — already, today. Everything else in these thirty days is simply learning to live like the new creation you already are.`,
