    walk: `There is a question that quietly haunts every new believer: Did I do enough? Am I good enough for God to keep me? And here, on Day 2, God answers it once and for all. You were not saved because you were good enough. You were saved by grace — God's undeserved, freely given love.

Grace means a gift. And a gift is not earned, or it wouldn't be a gift. You didn't buy your salvation with good behavior, and you can't lose it with a bad day. Jesus paid the whole price. All you did was open your hands and receive what He already finished.

This matters more than you know, friend. Because the enemy of your soul will whisper that God's love is a wage you have to keep earning — that one slip and you're cut off. That is a lie. If your standing with God depended on your performance, you would never have peace. But it depends on His gift, and His gifts don't get taken back.

So you can exhale. You are not on probation. You are not auditioning. You are saved — not by what you do, but by what Jesus did. Let that settle the restless place in you. The pressure is off. Now you get to follow Him not to earn His love, but because you already have it.`,
