    walk: `Of all the things you became the moment you believed, this may be the most tender: you became a child of God. Not a servant kept at a distance. Not a stranger hoping to be noticed. A son, a daughter — family.

Maybe the word father is hard for you. Maybe the one who was supposed to love you didn't, or wasn't there, or wounded you. If that's you, friend, hear this gently: God is not like that. He is the Father you always needed and never had. He doesn't leave. He doesn't lose His temper and withdraw. He runs toward His children, not away.

To "receive" Jesus and "believe on his name" — that's all it took. And in that moment, God didn't just forgive you; He adopted you. He wrote your name into His family with no plans of ever crossing it out. You didn't earn a place at His table; you were given one, freely, as His own.

This is your new identity, and it's deeper than anything that's ever defined you — deeper than your past, your failures, your reputation, your name. Before you are anything else now, you are a child of God. Let that be the truth you stand on when you don't know who you are anymore. You belong to Him.`,
