    walk: `Sooner or later — maybe already — you're going to do something you know grieves God. And in that moment, the enemy will tell you to run and hide, to stay away from God until you feel clean enough to come back. That instinct will kill your walk if you let it. So learn this verse early, friend, and lean on it your whole life.

When you sin, you don't hide from God — you come to Him. You confess it, which simply means you agree with Him about it, no excuses and no hiding. And what does He do? He is faithful and just to forgive. Faithful — He always does it. Just — because Jesus already paid for that sin, God is not overlooking it; He's applying the payment Christ made.

And He doesn't just forgive — He cleanses you from all unrighteousness. Not some of it. All of it. You don't have to carry the residue of shame around afterward. When God forgives, He makes you clean, like it never happened.

This is the rhythm of a healthy walk with Jesus: not sinless perfection, but quick honesty. You'll stumble; you confess; He forgives and cleanses; you keep walking. Don't let one fall become a week of hiding. The path back to God is always short — it's one honest prayer away.`,
