    walk: `Years of hard living can turn a heart to stone. You stop feeling. You build walls. You protect yourself by going numb, because feeling hurt too much. Maybe you came to Jesus with a heart like that — guarded, tired, hardened by everything you've survived.

Here is God's promise to you: I will take away the stony heart, and give you an heart of flesh. He doesn't just change what you do; He changes what you are on the inside. A heart of flesh is a heart that can feel again — that can be moved by love, broken by what breaks God's heart, softened toward people you once kept out.

You may already be noticing it. Tears that come more easily. A tenderness toward others you didn't used to have. A conscience that's awake again. That's not weakness, friend — that's God keeping His promise. He is giving you a new heart, and a soft heart is a sign of life, not fragility.

Let Him keep doing this gentle surgery. Don't rush back behind the old walls when feeling things gets uncomfortable. The hardness kept the pain out, but it kept the love out too. God is giving you back the ability to live fully — to love, to grieve, to hope. Trust Him with your softened heart. He'll guard it better than your walls ever did.`,
