    walk: `You're walking a new path, friend, and you can't always see far ahead. That's where God's Word comes in. The Bible is not a dusty rulebook — it is a lamp and a light, given to show you where to put your feet on a road you've never walked before.

Notice it says a lamp unto your feet and a light unto your path — not a floodlight that shows the whole journey at once. God usually gives just enough light for the next step. That can be frustrating when you want the whole map, but it's actually a mercy. It keeps you walking close to Him, depending on Him for tomorrow's light tomorrow.

The Word does something to you when you spend time in it. It feeds you. It steadies you. It answers the lies in your head with truth. It shows you who God is and who you now are. A believer who doesn't read the Bible is like a traveler walking in the dark — stumbling, anxious, easily lost. But the one who lives in the Word always has light for the next step.

You don't have to read it all at once or understand everything. Start small — a chapter, a few verses, even a single verse you carry through the day. The Gospel of John is a beautiful place to begin. Let the light in a little each day, and watch how it steadies your steps.`,
