    title: "He Hears You",
    ref: "1 John 5:14",
    scripture: "And this is the confidence that we have in him, that, if we ask any thing according to his will, he heareth us.",
    walk: `Yesterday you learned to pray. Today, learn this: when you pray, God actually hears you. Your prayers don't bounce off the ceiling. They don't get lost. The God of all the universe leans in and listens to you — that's the confidence this verse gives.

Sometimes we wonder if prayer even does anything. Nothing seems to change; the heavens feel silent. But silence is not the same as absence. God hears every prayer, even the ones that seem to go unanswered. And He answers in His way and His timing, which is always wiser and kinder than ours — sometimes yes, sometimes no, sometimes wait, but never I didn't hear you.

The verse adds according to his will, and that's a gift, not a limitation. It means you can pray boldly, knowing God will lovingly filter your requests through what's truly best. You don't have to be afraid of asking wrong. Ask freely, then trust Him to answer rightly. A good Father doesn't give His child everything they ask for — He gives what's good.

So keep praying, friend, even when you can't see results yet. Your prayers matter. They move things you cannot see. And the One who hears you loves you too much to ever ignore you. Talk to Him today like the listening Father He is — because He is listening.`,
