    scripture: "Be still, and know that I am God: I will be exalted among the heathen, I will be exalted in the earth.",
    walk: `You've reached the end of week two, and here God gives you a command that feels almost too gentle to be a command: Be still. In a loud, hurried, anxious world, learning to be still before God is one of the most important things you'll ever learn.

To "be still" is to stop striving, stop scrambling, stop trying to control everything, and simply rest in the truth that He is God — and you are not. So much of our anxiety comes from carrying weight that was never ours to carry, trying to be the god of our own lives. Stillness lays that burden down. It says, God, You're in charge, and I trust You.

This is not laziness, friend — it's trust. The stillest, most peaceful people are not the ones with the fewest problems; they're the ones who have learned to be quiet before a God they trust. When you sit still in His presence, even for a few minutes, something settles in you. The noise dies down. You remember who's really running things.

Try it. Find a few quiet minutes today — no phone, no noise, no agenda. Just sit, breathe, and say slowly, "Be still… and know… that You are God." You don't have to fill the silence with words. Let Him meet you in the quiet. In stillness, you remember that the God who holds the whole world is holding you, too.`,
