    walk: `The old life is behind you, and God invites you to walk in newness of life. Notice the word walk. The new life isn't just something that happened to you once — it's a way of living, step after step, day after day. You don't just have new life; you walk in it.

This verse paints a beautiful picture: your old self was buried with Christ, and just as Jesus rose from the grave, you rose to a brand-new life. The person who was ruled by sin, fear, and shame — that person was laid in the tomb with Christ. The person who walked out is new, raised by the same power that raised Jesus from the dead.

But here's the honest part, friend: new life takes practice. You'll still feel the pull of old habits, old ways of thinking, old reactions. That's normal. Walking in newness means that, more and more, you choose the new way — the way of honesty over hiding, love over bitterness, trust over fear. Each choice is a step. Some days you'll walk well; some days you'll stumble. Keep walking.

You are not trying to become someone new by willpower. You already are new in Christ; now you're simply learning to live like it. The power that raised Jesus lives in you. So take the next step today in the new direction. That's the whole walk — one new step at a time.`,
